Sorry for the long thread, but these tips have helped me through the difficulties of school, and food shit. I hope this helps some of you!!

19. go on lots of walks
 ♡ going on a walk outside refreshes your brain and burns cals!! If you can’t go outside, even walking around your house can help.

— and what you were doing). it was a second ago. you don’t need food in such a short time period, your brain is just wired to think you do.
 ♡ if you can control the psychological aspect of it all, the physical feeling will mean nothing. Hunger is an illusion

18. Keep that same mentality with food. time only means something if we make it, so 24 or 72 hours without food should be a cake walk, 72 hours ago was tuesday night, coming home and crying in your skirt and sweater (this was super specific lmfao, but just think ab 3 days ago—

—it’s fine, there have been worse students who have gone on to do great things. 
 ♡ this applies to food too. Don’t repeat shitty behavior just because you’ve done it in the past. Make the change and lose the weight

17. feel no shame. there’s no going back, so all we can do is look forward. this shame actually just makes it worse for yourself in the future because you are already expecting a fuck up from yourself. let it go. —

16. it’s just work. think about the amount of time from when you get out of the car in the morning to when you walk back out to it after school is out. it feels instantaneous. just don’t give time meaning and rip through your shit.
 ♡ gotta think ab it philosophically sometimes

— so you aren’t falling asleep during your second work day.
 ♡ this was specific to my schedule, but just manage your time in a deliberate and well thought out fashion. It can make all the difference.

15. Try to fit everything into assigned days, but play it by ear. if you get to the end of saturday and you have almost nothing done, staying up late might be the best bet. but if you’re just falling a little behind, prioritize a good nights sleep and stay up late tomorrow, —

14. keep laundry going for excuses to take miniature breaks every now and then
 ♡ I have way too many clothes, so I always have laundry

13. put on comfortable clothes
 ♡ if I have uncomfy clothes on, that is my second focus point, and I can’t properly do work. Maybe I’m just nitpicky

12. under no circumstance may you take a nap. if you are feeling even a lick of tired in you, drink some fucking coffee bitch.
 ♡ maybe the power naps work for you guys, but for me if I fall asleep for a second, it’s over, I might as well have time traveled to the next morning.

11. tidy up your desk
 ♡ I never believed the whole a clear space is a clear mind, but then I started tidying the area I would have to look at while working and saw a significant improvement in my work flow. Stay tidy. (just as far as you need to look)

10. do not to bring food into your space
 ♡ this leads to mindless eating

9. don’t exceed your breaks
 ♡ you say 15 more minutes, and then it’s suddenly been 2 extra hours.

8. keep music on!!
 ♡ I personally always need 2 things going, because that’s my brains limit. So I’ll play mindless tv or a movie I’ve seen a billion times or music while doing hw always so I can only focus on those two things, and there is no room for a third (eg, my phone)

7. ONLY use your phone to play music and when you need to look something VERY SPECIFIC up
♡ it is disgustingly easy to go on your phone to look up something and then you look up and it’s been 3 hours. DONT allow an opportunity for this to happen

6. switch up your location if you need
 ♡ this can help refresh your brain and get you out of a mind block

5. (I made an itinerary of EXACTLY what order to do everything, and how I was gonna split it up and the size of breaks and everything)
 ♡ stick to the itinerary, i made it with specific intent

4. drink lots of black coffee!
 ♡ energy is a MUST, there is no way around that. I got used to black coffee through drinking it constantly while doing work

3. drink tea in place of food
 ♡ clams u down, and can help with focus

2. up the water intake
 ♡ always have some water next to you to sip on

1. let skinniness be a guide
 ♡ every time you think about food, do an assignment instead

♥*♡∞:｡.｡ study+starving tips I made for myself when I had 50 late assignments to do in 48 hours last year ｡.｡:∞♡*♥
